}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 1.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   His consciousness returned after his swoon, Dante begins to investigate his new \softline
surroundings.  Once again we are not told how he moved (or was moved) from one Circle to the \softline
next, from Lust to Gluttony.  However, unlike the situation that pertained in the commentaries in \softline
response to the questions raised about the means of his crossing Acheron, the undescribed \softline
transport here has not caused debate, nor even any particular interest.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab For the Ovidian source of the phrase 'Al tornar de la mente' (With my returning senses) \softline
see Francesco Mazzoni, }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Il canto VI dell'"Inferno"}{\plain \fs24 \f1  in }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Nuove letture dantesche}{\plain \fs24 \f1  (Florence: Le \softline
Monnier, 1967), p. 19: }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Metam}{\plain \fs24 \f1 . VI.531, 'Ubi mens rediit,' cited along with Brunetto Latini, \softline
}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Tesoretto}{\plain \fs24 \f1 , verse 191, 'Ma tornando a la mente....'}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1  }{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 2.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   As many commentators now point out, the technical word for 'in-laws' (}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 cognati}{\plain \fs24 \f1 ) used \softline
here reminds the reader who has become caught up in Francesca's words (as was the protagonist) \softline
